 154:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 155:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** /** @defgroup RCC_Group1 Internal and external clocks, PLL, CSS and MCO configuration functions
 156:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  *  @brief   Internal and external clocks, PLL, CSS and MCO configuration functions 
 157:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  *
 158:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** @verbatim   
 159:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  ===================================================================================
 160:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  ##### Internal and  external clocks, PLL, CSS and MCO configuration functions #####
 161:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  ===================================================================================
 162:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****     [..]
 163:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       This section provide functions allowing to configure the internal/external clocks,
 164:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       PLLs, CSS and MCO pins.
 165:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   
 166:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) HSI (high-speed internal), 16 MHz factory-trimmed RC used directly or through
 167:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           the PLL as System clock source.
 168:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 169:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) LSI (low-speed internal), 32 KHz low consumption RC used as IWDG and/or RTC
 170:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           clock source.
 171:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 172:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) HSE (high-speed external), 4 to 26 MHz crystal oscillator used directly or
 173:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           through the PLL as System clock source. Can be used also as RTC clock source.
 174:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 175:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) LSE (low-speed external), 32 KHz oscillator used as RTC clock source.   
 176:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 177:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) PLL (clocked by HSI or HSE), featuring two different output clocks:
 178:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****         (++) The first output is used to generate the high speed system clock (up to 168 MHz)
 179:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****         (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for the USB OTG FS (48 MHz),
 180:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****              the random analog generator (<=48 MHz) and the SDIO (<= 48 MHz).
 181:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 182:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) PLLI2S (clocked by HSI or HSE), used to generate an accurate clock to achieve 
 183:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           high-quality audio performance on the I2S interface or SAI interface in case 
 184:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           of STM32F429x/439x devices.
 185:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****      
 186:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) PLLSAI clocked by (HSI or HSE), used to generate an accurate clock to SAI 
 187:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           interface and LCD TFT controller available only for STM32F42xxx/43xxx/446xx/469xx/479xx d
 188:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   
 189:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) CSS (Clock security system), once enable and if a HSE clock failure occurs 
 190:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****          (HSE used directly or through PLL as System clock source), the System clock
 191:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****          is automatically switched to HSI and an interrupt is generated if enabled. 
 192:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****          The interrupt is linked to the Cortex-M4 NMI (Non-Maskable Interrupt) 
 193:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****          exception vector.   
 194:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 195:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) MCO1 (microcontroller clock output), used to output HSI, LSE, HSE or PLL
 196:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           clock (through a configurable prescaler) on PA8 pin.
 197:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** 
 198:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****       (#) MCO2 (microcontroller clock output), used to output HSE, PLL, SYSCLK or PLLI2S
 199:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****           clock (through a configurable prescaler) on PC9 pin.
 200:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****  @endverbatim
 201:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @{
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccEdY3aN.s 			page 5


 202:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   */
