1437:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c **** /**
1438:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @brief  Configures the RTC clock (RTCCLK).
1439:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @note   As the RTC clock configuration bits are in the Backup domain and write
1440:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         access is denied to this domain after reset, you have to enable write
1441:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         access using PWR_BackupAccessCmd(ENABLE) function before to configure
1442:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         the RTC clock source (to be done once after reset).    
1443:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @note   Once the RTC clock is configured it can't be changed unless the  
1444:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         Backup domain is reset using RCC_BackupResetCmd() function, or by
1445:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         a Power On Reset (POR).
1446:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *    
1447:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @param  RCC_RTCCLKSource: specifies the RTC clock source.
1448:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
1449:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *            @arg RCC_RTCCLKSource_LSE: LSE selected as RTC clock
1450:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *            @arg RCC_RTCCLKSource_LSI: LSI selected as RTC clock
1451:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *            @arg RCC_RTCCLKSource_HSE_Divx: HSE clock divided by x selected
1452:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *                                            as RTC clock, where x:[2,31]
1453:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *  
1454:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @note   If the LSE or LSI is used as RTC clock source, the RTC continues to
1455:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         work in STOP and STANDBY modes, and can be used as wakeup source.
1456:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         However, when the HSE clock is used as RTC clock source, the RTC
1457:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         cannot be used in STOP and STANDBY modes.    
1458:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @note   The maximum input clock frequency for RTC is 1MHz (when using HSE as
1459:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *         RTC clock source).
1460:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   *  
1461:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   * @retval None
1462:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_rcc.c ****   */
